--- In junit@y..., Toby Ferguson &lt;toby.h.ferguson@s...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Peter,
&gt; 
&gt; private is private - so if these methods truly are private then 
noone can
&gt; get at them.
&gt; 
&gt; However, one technique is to use an inner class that gives access 
to the
&gt; methods to be tested, and then to not include that class when 
publishing the
&gt; final code.
&gt; 
&gt; For example, here is some class with a private method (I&#39;ve 
attached the
&gt; classes too, in case this gets garbled as text)
&gt; 
&gt; public class PrivateMethod
&gt; {
&gt;   private String value =  &quot;foo&quot;;
&gt; 
&gt;   private String getValue(){
&gt;  return value;
&gt;   }
&gt; 
&gt;   private void setValue(String v){
&gt;  this.value = v;
&gt;   }
&gt; 
&gt;   public class Test
&gt;   {
&gt;  public String getValue(){
&gt;    return value;
&gt;  }
&gt;  public void setValue(String v){
&gt;    value = v;
&gt;  }
&gt;   }
&gt; }
&gt; Note the inner &quot;Test&quot; class exposing public versions of the private 
get/set
&gt; methods ...
&gt; 
&gt; Here&#39;s a TestPrivateMethod class which will show how to use the 
inner
&gt; PrivateMethod.Test class:
&gt; 
&gt; import junit.framework.TestCase;
&gt; import junit.framework.TestSuite;
&gt; import junit.textui.TestRunner;
&gt; 
&gt; public class TestPrivateMethod extends TestCase
&gt; {
&gt; 
&gt;   public TestPrivateMethod(String name){
&gt;  super(name);
&gt;   }
&gt; 
&gt;   public static void main(String [] args){
&gt;  TestRunner.run(new TestSuite(TestPrivateMethod.class));
&gt;   }
&gt; 
&gt;    /** Will not compile!
&gt;   public void testPrivateGet(){
&gt;  PrivateMethod p = new PrivateMethod();
&gt;  assertEquals(p.getValue(), &quot;foo&quot;);
&gt;   }
&gt;    */
&gt; 
&gt;   public void testPrivateGetViaInnerClass(){
&gt;  PrivateMethod p = new PrivateMethod();
&gt;  PrivateMethod.Test pt = p.new Test();
&gt;  assertEquals(&quot;foo&quot;, pt.getValue());
&gt;   }
&gt; 
&gt;   public void testPrivateSetViaInnerClass(){
&gt;  PrivateMethod p = new PrivateMethod();
&gt;  PrivateMethod.Test pt = p.new Test();
&gt;  final String nv = &quot;new value&quot;;
&gt;  pt.setValue(nv);
&gt;  assertEquals( nv, pt.getValue());
&gt;   }
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; 
